item.title: [ISS-224] Cannot Import PerfectLib under Xcode 8 beta 2 and OS X 10.11.5/6 (Added Reproducing Repo)
item.description:
Clone this bug reproducing repo and try to swift build.

https://github.com/ShaneQi/PerfectBugReproducing

In this repo, I added Perfect-URL and Perfect-HTTPServer as dependencies.
There is barely anything in the Sources: only a import PerfectLib.

Under my env (OS X 10.11.5/6, Xcode 8 beta 2), this repo can't be built.

item.summary: Cannot Import PerfectLib under Xcode 8 beta 2 and OS X 10.11.5/6 (Added Reproducing Repo)

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
And the same project can be compiled on Ubuntu 14.04 with swift 3.0 preview 2. But I really need develop the project in Xcode.

It seems like some SDK is only available to 10.12, but my os is 10.11.

I found out this error only happens when I have Perfect-CURL dependency in Package.swift.

If I delete Perfect-CURL dependency from Package.swift, everything is good.

I uploaded a bug reproducing repo. Edited in the first issue post.

I asked a friend who has macOS 11.12 Sierra, try to build the reproducing project. He succeeded.

So I assert this issue as a compatibility issue between Swift 3 and El Capitan.

I'm closing the issue.
